SUMMARY:Free Watch Party: Mexico vs Korea Republic
DTSTAMP:20260619T133503Z
DTSTART:20260618T183000Z
DESCRIPTION:El Tri returns to the pitch with the whole nation watching. The
	 pressure is on! Korea Republic brings speed\, discipline\, and a hunger f
	or upset. Two passionate soccer cultures collide in the game\, and it is g
	oing to be one for the books. \nThe festival gates open at 6:30 p.m. to th
	e sounds of DJ Cris. Kickoff is at 8:00 p.m. Admission is free!  \nFood an
	d Beverage Concessions: Enjoy a variety of festival food fare\, beer and w
	ine\, and non-alcoholic beverages from Coca-Cola. Visit Smalls Sliders for
	 burgers\, fries\, and shakes and cool down with Frios Gourmet Pops. Stop 
	by Hearsay’s festival tent for a cold beer or beer bucket or grab a michel
	ada\, wine\, or beer from Gaspacho’s festival tent. Non-alcoholic drinks f
	rom Coca-Cola as well as pre-packaged snacks can be purchased at the Commu
	nity Partner Concessions Booth\, proceeds benefiting Levy Park and the eve
	nt’s community partners. \nFace Painting & Henna Art: Get into the tournam
	ent spirit with face and body art from Magic Faces by Shay and Henna Stati
	on & Glitter Bar \nCommunity Partners and Volunteers: Levy Park is represe
	nting a wide array of non-profit park partners for this event. All sales g
	enerated at the Community Partner Concessions booth will support Levy Park
	’s maintenance and operation. Email us to learn more about volunteer oppor
	tunities. \nArt Installations and Photo Opportunities: Commemorate the exp
	erience with a photo tour of the park\, including life-sized soccer-themed
	 photo backdrops and a tournament bracket. Visit our soccer ball music box
	 and turn the crank for festive sounds. \nMerchandise: Event merchandise c
	elebrating Houston\, Levy Park\, and the global soccer tournament will als
	o be available for purchase. \nFestival Guidelines: \nVISITORS MUST COMPLY
	 WITH DIRECTIONS FROM PARK PERSONNEL\, OR THEY WILL BE ASKED TO LEAVE THE 
	PARK. PARENTS ARE RESPONSIBLE FOR THEIR CHILDREN’S SAFETY IN THE PARK. \nC
	HAIRS AND SEATING: No outside furniture. Blankets may be brought into the 
	Festival site for the designated blanket seating area. All other furniture
	 is available on a first-come\, first-served basis. \nSTROLLERS & WAGONS: 
	Oversized strollers and wagons may need to be parked in a designated area 
	during the festival. All visitors must comply with park personnel regardin
	g stroller and wagon parking. \nFOOD AND BEVERAGES: Guests are permitted t
	o enter with one factory-sealed bottle of water. Outside food and drinks a
	re prohibited (exceptions will be made for baby food and necessary medical
	 dietary food items). A variety of food\, non-alcoholic drinks\, beer\, an
	d wine will be available for purchase from Festival concessionaires. \nRE-
	ENTRY: If you leave the Festival site\, you will be re-screened before re-
	entry.  \nTHE FOLLOWING ARE PROHIBITED: \n\nSmoking or Vaping\nUmbrellas\n
	Drug Use\nKites and Drones\nRecreational Motorized Vehicles\nGuns\, knives
	\, any weaponry\nSoliciting\nBikes\, scooters\, rollerblades\, and roller 
	skates\n\nhttps://www.levyparkhouston.org/events/mexico-korea-republic/\n\
	nFrom Levy Park Houston
URL:https://www.levyparkhouston.org/events/mexico-korea-republic/
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:levy-park-houston
CATEGORIES:Levy Park Houston
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT5H
END:VEVENT
